---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Multi-Brand Portfolios in 2026';
const description = 'A practical guide to Shopify email apps for multi-brand portfolios, covering account separation, shared reporting, segmentation, pricing context, citations, and tradeoffs.';
const apps = [
['Sequenzy','Small operators managing focused brand sequences','Simple repeatable workflows','Limited portfolio-level complexity should be checked','https://sequenzy.com','Start with one brand and a reusable welcome or post-purchase sequence. Document the sender, audience, consent, and exit rules before cloning anything into a second store.'],
['Klaviyo','Portfolios needing deep brand-level segmentation','Rich events and configurable customer profiles','Governance and account structure require planning','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation','Klaviyo fits portfolios that need detailed behavior and brand-level event logic. Use hard brand boundaries, separate sending domains where appropriate, and audit shared profiles before enabling cross-brand personalization.'],
['Omnisend','Retail groups coordinating campaigns across brands','Accessible email and SMS automation','Brand-specific exceptions require QA','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/','Omnisend is practical for a group standardizing common retail journeys. Keep each brand’s creative, consent, and frequency policy explicit even when the workflow template is shared.'],
['Brevo','Portfolios combining lifecycle and transactional email','Broad messaging toolkit','More manual separation and reporting','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/','Brevo can support a multi-brand program when streams and sender identities are separated. Build a reporting layer that preserves brand context rather than aggregating away important differences.'],
['Drip','DTC groups comparing repeat purchase by brand','Commerce automation and reporting','Less appropriate for mixed non-commerce portfolios','https://www.drip.com/features','Drip suits portfolios where each brand is ecommerce-led and repeat purchase is the main shared question. Compare cohorts only after product timing and margin differences are accounted for.'],
['Shopify Email','Small portfolios keeping brands operationally separate','Native campaign and product setup','Limited portfolio-level reporting','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing','Shopify Email works when each store can run its own simple program. It is safer for small portfolios that value clear separation over a centralized cross-brand automation layer.'],
['Mailchimp','Brand groups sharing editorial processes','Audiences, campaigns, and reusable templates','Shared audiences can create separation risk','https://mailchimp.com/features/email/','Mailchimp can fit a portfolio with centralized editorial support. Use separate audiences or carefully scoped tags, and prohibit accidental cross-brand sends by default.'],
['Customer.io','Technical portfolios with shared event infrastructure','Flexible event-triggered messaging','Engineering and governance investment are substantial','https://customer.io/product/messaging/','Customer.io is useful when multiple brands share event infrastructure but need brand-specific journeys. Include brand identity in every event and test that a retry cannot route a contact to the wrong sender.'],
['ActiveCampaign','Portfolios combining ecommerce with CRM follow-up','Automation and contact segmentation','Permissions and ownership require discipline','https://www.activecampaign.com/marketing-automation','ActiveCampaign suits groups where brand marketing overlaps with sales or account management. Define access, subscription types, and contact ownership before consolidating records.'],
['MailerLite','Small groups with straightforward brand newsletters','Forms, campaigns, and basic automation','Limited fit for complex portfolio structures','https://www.mailerlite.com/features','MailerLite is a good fit when each brand needs only a small newsletter and welcome path. Its low complexity makes review and separation easier for a lean operator.'],
['ConvertKit','Creator-led brand portfolios with education at the center','Subscriber sequences and broadcasts','Commerce and multi-store data depth is limited','https://convertkit.com/features','ConvertKit works when brands share a creator voice but still have distinct editorial promises. Keep subscriber expectations and commercial identity clear for each brand.'],
['GetResponse','Portfolios combining brands with events or landing pages','Automation, landing pages, and event tools','Broader suite adds administration','https://www.getresponse.com/features','GetResponse is useful when portfolio brands share event infrastructure or lead-generation formats. Separate registration, attendance, and purchase data by brand before creating reusable follow-up.'],
['HubSpot','Groups coordinating marketing, service, and sales','CRM-connected marketing and account context','Cost and administration can be substantial','https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing','HubSpot makes sense when the portfolio needs shared CRM visibility without shared promotional consent. Define brand ownership and subscription types before activating cross-brand workflows.']
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">A multi-brand operator needs economies of scale without accidental cross-brand messaging. The platform should make separation, permissions, sender identity, consent, and reporting visible to the team.</p><p>We prioritize brand isolation, reusable patterns, portfolio-level learning, and clean ownership. Confirm current account, seat, and billing structures from official documentation before consolidating stores.</p><h2>Shortlist by portfolio need</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for multi-brand portfolios</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[5]}</p><p><strong>Pros:</strong> {a[2]}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {a[3]}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> verify official plans for brands, contacts, sends, seats, SMS, and implementation at the <a href={a[4]} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a>. Pilot one brand first, then add another only after checking data separation, sender identity, consent, and deliverability.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros in practice</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Risk to manage</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Evidence to review</th><td>Brand routing, audience isolation, sender identity, permissions, deliverability, and comparable cohort results.</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Portfolio priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Lean repeated sequences</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Focused workflows reduce maintenance.</td></tr><tr><td>Deep brand-level event logic</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible profiles and segments.</td></tr><tr><td>Brand-level repeat-purchase analysis</td><td>Drip</td><td>Commerce reporting orientation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Continue with the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/deliverability">deliverability guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
